Sentencas: This paper presents electrochemical impedance simulation of a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode in order to investigate the effect of mass transport processes on the impedance spectra.
Titulo: The effect of mass transfer on electrochemical impedance of a solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The current model takes in to account the gas-phase transport processes both in the gas channel and within the porous electrode and couples the gas transport processes with the electrochemical kinetics.
Titulo: The effect of mass transfer on electrochemical impedance of a solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The impedance simulation is carried out in time domain, and the correlation between the anode harmonic responses to the sinusoidal excitation and the impedance spectra is analyzed.
Titulo: The effect of mass transfer on electrochemical impedance of a solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: In order to solve the system of non-linear equations, an in-house code based on the finite difference method is developed and utilized.
Titulo: The effect of mass transfer on electrochemical impedance of a solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: Results show a depressed semicircle in the Nyquist plot, which originates from gas transport processes in the gas channel, in addition to a Warburg diffusion impedance originates from gas transport in the thick porous anode.
Titulo: The effect of mass transfer on electrochemical impedance of a solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The influence of parameters such as electrode thickness, inlet gas composition, and temperature is also investigated and the results are discussed.
Titulo: The effect of mass transfer on electrochemical impedance of a solid oxide fuel cell anode

Sentencas: The simulation results are in good agreement with published data.
Titulo: The effect of mass transfer on electrochemical impedance of a solid oxide fuel cell anode
